entry.title: The Food Standards Act 1999 (Commencement No. 2) Order 2000
entry.summary: This Order brings the Food Safety Act 1999 into force, in so far as it is not already in force.

entry.title: The Public Processions (Northern Ireland) Act 1998 (Accounts and Audit) Order 2000
entry.summary: This Order changes the accounting cycle by which the Parades Commission is required to complete its accounts from the 12 months ending on the 31st December in any year to the 12 months ending on the 31st March in any year.

entry.title: The Housing Benefit (General) Amendment Regulations 2000
entry.summary: These Regulations amend regulation 5 of the Housing Benefit (General) Regulations 1987 (S.I. 1987/1971) (circumstances in which a person is or is not to be treated as occupying a dwelling as his home).

The National Health Service Supplies Authority (Establishment and Constitution) Amendment Order 2000
entry.summary: This Order changes the name of the National Health Service Supplies Authority, a Special Health Authority established under section 11 of the National Health Authority Act 1977, to the National Health Service Logistics Authority. It also makes transitional provision.

entry.title: The National Health Service (Charges to Overseas Visitors) Amendment Regulations 2000
entry.summary: These Regulations amend the National Health Service (Charges to Overseas Visitors) Regulations 1989 (“the 1989 Regulations”).

entry.title: The Welfare Reform and Pensions Act 1999 (Commencement No. 3) Order 2000
entry.summary: This Order brings into force on 3rd April 2000 section 10 of the Welfare Reform and Pensions Act 1999 (which amends section 49 of the Pensions Act 1995 (c. 26) in relation to the payments to be made by employers into occupational pension schemes), in so far as it is not already in force by virtue of section 89(5) of that Act of 1999.

entry.title: The Local Authorities (Members' Allowances) (Amendment) (England) (No. 2) Regulations 2000
entry.summary: These Regulations further amend the Local Authorities (Members' Allowances) Regulations 1991. They apply only in relation to local authorities in England.

entry.summary: These Regulations further amend the Local Authorities (Members' Allowances) Regulations 1991. They apply only in relation to local authorities and other bodies in England.

entry.title: The Air Passenger Duty and Other Indirect Taxes (Interest Rate) (Amendment) Regulations 2000
entry.summary: These Regulations, which come into force on 1st April 2000, make a number of changes to the Air Passenger Duty and Other Indirect Taxes (Interest Rate) Regulations 1998 (S.I. 1998/1461) (“the principal Regulations”). The principal Regulations are amended so that they will specify the rate of interest applicable for the purposes of the additional enactments to which section 197 of the Finance Act 1996 applies following its amendment by paragraph 21 of Schedule 5 to the Finance Act 1997 and section 130 of the Finance Act 1999. These amendments extended section 197 to cover interest on amounts repayable in respect of overpayments by the Commissioners of Customs and Excise (“ the Commissioners”) in connection with excise duties, insurance premium tax and landfill tax; and interest payable to and by the Commissioners in connection with customs duty.

entry.title: The National Health Service (Injury Benefits) Amendment Regulations 2000

ukm:Subject.Value: NATIONAL HEALTH SERVICE, ENGLAND AND WALES

category.term: NATIONAL HEALTH SERVICE, ENGLAND AND WALES

entry.summary: These Regulations further amend the National Health Service (Injury Benefits) Regulations 1995 (“the 1995 Regulations”) which provide for the payment, by the Secretary of State for Health, of injury benefits to or in respect of any person engaged in the National Health Service in England and Wales whose earning ability is reduced, or who dies, as a result of an injury suffered, or a disease contracted, in the course of his or her duties.

entry.title: The National Health Service (General Medical Services) Amendment (No. 2) Regulations 2000
entry.summary: These Regulations further amend the National Health Service (General Medical Services) Regulations 1992 (“the 1992 Regulations”), which regulate the terms on which General Medical Services are provided under the National Health Service Act 1977.

entry.title: The National Health Service (Dental Charges) (Scotland) Amendment Regulations 2000
entry.summary: These Regulations amend the National Health Service (Dental Charges) (Scotland) Regulations 1989 (“the principal Regulations”), which provide for the making and recovery of charges for dental appliances supplied or repaired under the National Health Service in Scotland, and for other dental treatment provided as part of NHS general dental services.

entry.title: The Welfare of Animals (Transport) (Electronic Route Plans Pilot Schemes) (England) Order 2000
entry.summary: This Order provides for the creation of pilot schemes (referred to throughout this Order as “ERP pilot schemes”) in order to test modes of electronic submission for route plans required under article 13 of the Welfare of Animals (Transport) Order 1997 (S.I. 1997/1480, which implements Council Directive 91/628/EC (OJ No. L 340, 11.12.1991, p. 17) as last amended by Council Directive 95/29/EC (OJ No. L 148, 30.6.1995, p.52)) (referred to throughout this Order as “the 1997 Order”).

entry.summary: These Regulations amend the National Health Service (Optical Charges and Payments) (Scotland) Regulations 1998 (“the principal Regulations”) which provide for payments to be made by means of a voucher system, in respect of costs incurred by certain categories of persons in connection with the supply, replacement and repair of optical appliances.
